## Description

Exists the class Color that stores the color value in RGBA format. Each parameter (red, green, blue, and alpha) determines the intensity of a color from 0 to 255.

## Task

You need to write the function that takes an id and returns the class Color, whose values are generated in accordance with id.

### Example:
```c++
uint32_t id = 2139062143;
Color res = getColorByID(id);
res == Color { 127, 127, 127, 127 }; // true
```

----

### Class Color Example:
```c++
Color color1 { rgba };
Color color2 { r, g, b, a };

color1.getR(); 
color1.getG();
color1.getB();
color1.getA();

color1.setR(r); 
color1.setG(g);
color1.setB(b);
color1.setA(a);
color1.setRGBA(rgba);
color1.setRGBA(r, g, b, a);

bool res = color1 == color2;
```

```c++
class Color final {
private:
	using UCHAR = unsigned char;

private:
	UCHAR r, g, b, a;

public:
	Color() = delete;
	Color(const Color& color);
	Color(const UCHAR& rgba);
	Color(const UCHAR& _r, const UCHAR& _g,
		  const UCHAR& _b, const UCHAR& _a);
	~Color() = default;

	bool operator==(const Color& rhs);

	UCHAR getR();
	UCHAR getG();
	UCHAR getB();
	UCHAR getA();

	void setR(const UCHAR& _r);
	void setG(const UCHAR& _g);
	void setB(const UCHAR& _b);
	void setA(const UCHAR& _a);

	void setRGBA(const UCHAR& rgba);
	void setRGBA(const UCHAR& _r, const UCHAR& _g,
				 const UCHAR& _b, const UCHAR& _a);
};
```
